      "comment": "FREMARKS PEGGY (1) put the writing on the wall with three successive placings then gave her opponents no chance last start when she cruised to a 24 metre victory at Ballarat. Likely to get all the favours from the ace draw and races well here so can back that up. BETTOR MAN (4) made a winning return at his latest appearance two weeks ago, coming from a wider barrier and getting home by 2 metres at Ballarat. It's never easy stepping up out of maiden grad but he'll be fitter and is clearly back in good order. WAIKARE ADRIENNA (9) led and faded to midfield as favourite last start but had finished runner-up in her previous two outings so is worth another chance. MIDNITE MUSCLE (3) draws lower than when third behind FREMARKS PEGGY last start.",
